+# bujjictl
+
+A lightweight, **local-first workflow orchestration engine** — think a tiny,
+single-machine Airflow / GitHub Actions. Define multi-step workflows in YAML,
+and `bujjictl` will build the dependency graph, run independent steps
+concurrently, handle retries / timeouts / env injection, and produce a
+structured JSON report of exactly what happened.
+
+Pure Python standard library. No runtime dependencies.
+
+---
+
+## Install
+
+```bash
+pip install .
+# or for development:
+pip install -e .
+```
+
+This installs the `bujjictl` console command. You can also run it without
+installing:
+
+```bash
+python -m bujjictl --help
+```
+
+---
+
+## Workflow file format
+
+```yaml
+name: my-workflow            # required
+description: optional text
+
+env:                         # optional: global env vars (merged into every step)
+  FOO: bar
+
+defaults:                    # optional: applied to every step unless overridden
+  timeout: 300               # seconds (float); omit for no timeout
+  retries: 0                 # extra attempts after the first
+  retry_backoff: 1.0         # seconds; exponential: delay * 2^(attempt-1)
+  shell: /bin/sh             # shell used to run `run:`
+
+steps:                       # required, non-empty list
+  - id: build                # required, unique, [A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_-]*
+    name: Build              # optional human label
+    run: |                   # required: shell script (use `|` for multi-line)
+      echo "building"
+      make build
+    depends_on:              # optional list of step ids
+      - fetch
+    env:                     # optional: step-level env (overrides global)
+      MODE: release
+    timeout: 60
+    retries: 2
+    retry_backoff: 0.5
+    shell: /bin/bash
+```
+
+### Injected environment variables
+
+Every step receives, in addition to the process environment + `env:` blocks:
+
+| Variable          | Meaning                              |
+|-------------------|--------------------------------------|
+| `BUJJI_WORKFLOW`  | The workflow `name`                  |
+| `BUJJI_STEP_ID`   | The current step's `id`              |
+| `BUJJI_ATTEMPT`   | 1-based attempt number for this step |
+
+### Execution semantics
+
+* The steps form a DAG via `depends_on`. Steps with no unmet dependencies are
+  scheduled immediately and run **concurrently** (bounded by `--max-workers`).
+* If a step **fails** or **times out** (after exhausting retries), every
+  transitive downstream step is marked `cancelled` and never runs.
+* Retries use exponential backoff: `retry_backoff * 2^(attempt-1)` seconds.
+* On timeout the step's process group is sent `SIGTERM`, then `SIGKILL`.
+
+### Validation
+
+`bujjictl validate` (and the start of every `run`) checks, **before executing
+anything**:
+
+* YAML is parseable (subset: mappings, lists, scalars, `|`/`>` block scalars,
+  comments, quoted strings — no anchors/flow collections).
+* Required fields present, correct types, no unknown keys.
+* Step ids are unique and well-formed.
+* Every `depends_on` references an existing step; no self-dependencies.
+* **No cycles** in the dependency graph.
+
+All problems are collected and reported together — not just the first one.
+
+---
+
+## Commands
+
+```text
+bujjictl validate <file.yaml>
+bujjictl run      <file.yaml> [-o report.json] [-j N] [--quiet] [--no-pretty]
+bujjictl report   <report.json> [--no-output]
+```
+
+* `validate` — parse + validate only. Exit 0 on success, 1 on error.
+* `run` — validate, execute, write a JSON report (default
+  `<name>.report.json`), then pretty-print it. Exit 0 on success, 1 on
+  validation error, 2 if any step did not succeed.
+* `report` — pretty-print a previously written JSON report.
+
+---
+
+## Report format
+
+```jsonc
+{
+  "workflow": { "name": "...", "description": "..." },
+  "status": "succeeded" | "failed",
+  "started_at": "2026-04-19T...Z",
+  "finished_at": "...",
+  "duration": 12.345,
+  "summary": { "succeeded": 4, "failed": 0, "timed_out": 0, "cancelled": 0, "total": 4 },
+  "steps": [
+    {
+      "id": "build",
+      "name": "Build",
+      "status": "succeeded" | "failed" | "timed_out" | "cancelled",
+      "depends_on": ["fetch"],
+      "started_at": "...",
+      "finished_at": "...",
+      "duration": 1.234,
+      "attempt_count": 2,
+      "cancel_reason": null,
+      "attempts": [
+        {
+          "number": 1,
+          "started_at": "...",
+          "finished_at": "...",
+          "duration": 0.61,
+          "exit_code": 1,
+          "timed_out": false,
+          "stdout": "...",
+          "stderr": "...",
+          "error": null
+        }
+      ]
+    }
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+## Quick start
+
+```bash
+python -m bujjictl validate examples/hello.yaml
+python -m bujjictl run examples/hello.yaml -o hello.report.json
+python -m bujjictl report hello.report.json
+```
